      <td>2-3 hours</td>
      <td>1-1.5 hours</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td><strong>Cleaning Cost</strong></td>
      <td>RM 80-120</td>
      <td>RM 50-80</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td><strong>Wear & Tear</strong></td>
      <td>Higher (kids, traffic)</td>
      <td>Lower</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td><strong>Replacement Frequency</strong></td>
      <td>Every 2-3 years</td>
      <td>Every 3-4 years</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td><strong>Damage Risk</strong></td>
      <td>Higher</td>
      <td>Lower</td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<p><strong>Operational cost:</strong> Family properties cost ~15-20% more to maintain.</p>

<h3>Guest Communication</h3>

<p><strong>Families:</strong></p>

<ul>
  <li>More questions beforehand (about kids, safety, etc.)</li>
  <li>More requests during stay (extra towels, etc.)</li>
  <li>Higher expectations for cleanliness</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Couples:</strong></p>

<ul>
  <li>Fewer questions</li>
  <li>More focus on experience/romance</li>
  <li>More likely to leave detailed reviews</li>
</ul>

<h2>Marketing: Different Approaches</h2>

<h3>Family Property Listing</h3>

<p><strong>Title examples:</strong></p>

<ul>
  <li>"Spacious 3BR Near Jonker Walk - Perfect for Families"</li>
  <li>"Family-Friendly Condo with Pool & Kids Amenities"</li>
  <li>"Sleeps 8: Kitchen, Washer, Netflix - Great for Groups"</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Key phrases to emphasize:</strong></p>

<ul>
  <li>"Family-friendly"</li>
  <li>"Kids welcome"</li>
  <li>"High chair + cot provided"</li>
  <li>"Condo pool"</li>
  <li>"Full kitchen"</li>
  <li>"Washer in unit"</li>
</ul>

<h3>Couples Property Listing</h3>

<p><strong>Title examples:</strong></p>

<ul>
  <li>"Romantic Sea View Suite - Perfect for Couples"</li>
  <li>"Cozy Studio with Balcony - Melaka UNESCO Zone"</li>
  <li>"Luxury 1BR with City Views - Weekend Escape"</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Key phrases to emphasize:</strong></p>

<ul>
  <li>"Couples retreat"</li>
  <li>"Romantic getaway"</li>
  <li>"Sea view"</li>
  <li>"Private balcony"</li>
  <li>"King bed"</li>
  <li>"Smart TV + Netflix"</li>
  <li>"Instagrammable"</li>
</ul>

<h2>Which Market Should You Choose?</h2>

<h3>Choose Family Market If:</h3>

<ul>
  <li>You have 3BR+ property</li>
  <li>Property is in resort area (with pool)</li>
  <li>You're comfortable with more wear and tear</li>
  <li>You prefer longer stays (more stable income)</li>
  <li>You want domestic market (school holidays)</li>
</ul>

<h3>Choose Couples Market If:</h3>

<ul>
  <li>You have 1-2BR property</li>
  <li>Property has great views or unique features</li>
  <li>You want higher nightly rates</li>
  <li>You prefer lower maintenance</li>
  <li>You want international market</li>
  <li>You can create romantic ambiance</li>
</ul>

<h2>Hybrid Approach: Can You Target Both?</h3>

<p><strong>Yes, with careful positioning:</strong></p>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Example:</strong> 2BR with king + twin beds</li>
  <li><strong>Marketing:</strong> "Perfect for couples OR small families"</li>
  <li><strong>Amenities:</strong> Include both romantic elements AND kid-friendly items</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Risk:</strong> Jack of all trades, master of none. May dilute your brand.</p>

<p><strong>Recommendation:</strong> Pick primary market, accept secondary bookings when they come.</p>

<h2>iHousing's Data: What Works Best</h2>

<h3>Best Performing Family Properties</h3>

<p>Common traits of top-earning family properties:</p>

<ul>
  <li>Located in resort condos (pool, facilities)</li>
  <li>3BR with 2 bathrooms</li>
  <li>Full kitchen + dining area</li>
  <li>Washer/dryer in unit</li>
  <li>Walking distance to family attractions</li>
  <li>Reviews mention "spacious" and "kid-friendly"</li>
</ul>

<h3>Best Performing Couples Properties</h3>

<p>Common traits of top-earning couples properties:</p>

<ul>
  <li>Stunning views (sea or heritage)</li>
  <li>King bed + quality linens</li>
  <li>Balcony with seating</li>
  <li>Modern, stylish decor</li>
  <li>Located in desirable area (UNESCO zone, beach)</li>
  <li>Reviews mention "romantic" and "perfect for couples"</li>
</ul>

<h2>Taking Action: Choose Your Market</h2>

<p><strong>WhatsApp iHousing today:</strong></p>

<ul>
  <li>Tell us your property details (size, layout, location)</li>
  <li>We'll recommend the best target market for your unit</li>
  <li>Get customized marketing strategy</li>
  <li>Start attracting the right guests within 7 days</li>
</ul>

<h2>The Bottom Line</h2>

<p>Both family and couples markets can be profitable in Melaka.</p>

<p><strong>Families:</strong> Larger market, longer stays, more operational effort.</p>

<p><strong>Couples:</strong> Higher rates, lower maintenance, more competition.</p>

<p><strong>The key:</strong> Choose ONE market and optimize everything for them. Don't try to be everything to everyone.</p>

<p><strong>WhatsApp iHousing today:</strong> Let us help you identify and dominate your target market.</p>
